          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Rural Hospital Access Act of 2015</b></p> <p>This bill amends title XVIII (Medicare) of the Social Security Act to make permanent the Medicare-dependent, small rural subsection (d) hospital program and increased payments under the Medicare low-volume hospital program.</p> <p> (Generally, a subsection [d] hospital is an acute care hospital, particularly one that receives payments under Medicare's inpatient prospective payment system [IPPS] when providing covered inpatient services to eligible beneficiaries.)]]></text>
        </item>
